<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Algeria Beats Sierra Leone 2-0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Algeria beat Sierra Leone
2-0 in the 20th African Nations' Cup group b soccer match at Free
State Stadium in Bloemfontein today.
</P>
<P>
Algeria's two goals were both scored by striker Ali Messabih
in the 45th and 63rd minutes. It is the first time for the north
Africa's desert warriors to defeat the west Africans since 1982
in the cup's history.
</P>
<P>
Both teams attacked the other from the very start, but the
difference between the two was Algeria's ability to finish their
attacks.
</P>
<P>
"Goal shooting is a great problem," said Sierra Leone's coach
Roger Palmgren speaking of his side.
</P>
<P>
"We can play the ball on to the goal line but we cannot
shoot," he added.
</P>
<P>
However, Algerian coach Ali Fergani attributed today's victory
to tactics.
</P>
<P>
Algeria is now leading group b with three points from the two
games, ahead of Sierra Leone two points from two games and Zambia
one point from one match.
</P>
<P>
Algeria and Zambia played to a goaless draw in the group b's
opening match on Sunday, while Sierra Leone defeated Burkina Faso
2-1 on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The 20th African Cup of Nations Soccer Tournament began on
January 13 in Johannesburg. Fifteen African teams took part in
the continent's biggest sports event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
