<HEADLINE> Chiluba Commends Fao's Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- President Frederick Chiluba
said today he has been impressed with the efforts by the Food and
Agriculture Organization (Fao) aimed at alleviating the suffering
of the people in the world.
</P>
<P>
While meeting visiting Fao Director-General Jacques Diouf
here, Chiluba expressed his government's full support needed to
assist the organization to attain its goals.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba said he has been following with keen interest Diouf's
ideas and successes as well as his projections in the organization
since taking office in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Zambia is proud of having an African as director-general of
the Fao because it makes it easier for African policies to be
projected to the international community, he added.
</P>
<P>
In reply, Diouf said his position has provided an opportunity
to represent views of the African continent to the organization.
</P>
<P>
He noted African presidents have a great duty in assisting his
organization to attain its programs by introducing sustainable
agriculture programs especially in the 44 African countries which
are hard hit by hunger.
</P>
<P>
Diouf arrived here today for a three-day visit to Zambia.
</P>
</TEXT>
