<HEADLINE> Polish President Says Integration with EU Is One of Poland's  Primary Objectives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 18 (Xinhua) -- President of Poland Aleksander
Kwasniewski said here today that integration with the European
Union(EU) has constantly been one of his country's primary
objectives.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with the President and the members of the
European Commission(EC) today in Brussels, Kwasniewski said that
EU's enlargement was the way of "securing a greater role for
Europe in global politics and the world economy".
</P>
<P>
In his address, he said that the accession of new countries to
the EU "should be seen as a process of historical and strategic
relevance for the whole of the continent, a process which will
reveal new perspectives and opportunities".
</P>
<P>
The Polish President said that Poland has already met a great
majority of the criteria for membership in the EU, adding that the
EU membership would provide an impetus for further development and
an instrument for strengthening his country's presence in the
international community.
</P>
<P>
"It is time... to start bilateral dialogue which will help the
Commission prepare the views for (accession) negotiations," he
said.
</P>
<P>
However, he urged that EU's principle of transparency of the
integration process "should be extended to the citizens of the
applicant countries".
</P>
<P>
Belgium is the last leg of the new Polish President's tour in
west Europe after visiting France and Germany.
</P>
<P>
During his visit here in Brussels, President Kwasniewski has
also met with NATO Secretary General Javier Solana, the King of
Belgium Alber II and Belgian Prime Minister Jean-Luc Dehaene.
</P>
</TEXT>
