<HEADLINE> Tanzanian President Calls For Closer Tanzania-Zaire Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, January 18 (Xinhua) -- President Benjamin Mkapa
has called for closer cooperation between Zaire and Tanzania in
an effort to ensure peace and stability in Rwanda and Burundi.
</P>
<P>
The president made the remarks while meeting with Zairean
Ambassador Pelendo Beledu Mawe here today, according to a
statement by the State House.
</P>
<P>
Mkapa said, as neighbours and most affected countries by the
waves of refugees from Rwanda and Burundi, Tanzania and Zaire
should maintain constant consultations in the search for lasting
solutions in the belligerent central African states.
</P>
<P>
Further more, the president urged cooperation among African
states in the poverty alleviation drive through trade and
exchange of experiences.
</P>
<P>
The Zairean ambassador expressed appreciation for the
president's initiatives of gearing the country towards economic
self-reliance, saying such a serious drive to end the shame of
poverty in Africa should be emulated by other states.  enditem

