<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OAU Makes Early Warning System Recommendation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of
African Unity (OAU) today "strongly recommends that the envisaged
early warning system should function under the exclusive control
and responsibility of the OAU and its policy making organs".
</P>
<P>
In a "summary record" adopted at the end of a four-day
seminar, the OAU said that "the seminar recommends close
monitoring of socio-economic indicators in order to plan for
early action".
</P>
<P>
Adverse socio-economic conditions and environmental
degradation have been manifested in many parts of Africa as
serious early warning signals, which require effective short and
long-term strategic planning for sustainable development,
the document said.
</P>
<P>
An early warning system would benefit the continent by
providing a framework for "actual and timeous implementaiton of
appropriate diplomatic and preventive action," according to the
document.
</P>
<P>
The OAU seminar also "recommends that the OAU should consider
publishing an annual survey of conflicts on the continent".
</P>
<P>
The organization appealed to the international community to
continue all possible financial and technical assistance to
ensure the realization of an early warning system in Africa and
other objectives of the OAU. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
