<HEADLINE> Meeting Between Angolan President, UNITA Leader Put Off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The meeting between Angolan
President Eduardo Dos Santos and former rebel leader Jonas
Savimbi scheduled for Saturday has been postponed.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by President Dos Santos here today after
his meeting with Madeleine Albright, the United States Ambassador
to the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The warring parties do not want to hold the summit in an
unfavourable atmosphere, the president said, adding the summit
will be held when progress is made in the peace process in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Both parties are negotiating on the date for the forthcoming
summit, he said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his hope that pace should be accelerated for the
troops assembly of the former rebel National Union for the Total
Independence of Angola (UNITA).
</P>
<P>
The forthcoming summit will be the fourth meeting between the
two leaders since late 1992, when civil war re-erupted in the
southern African country. They met three times in l995,
respectively in May, August and September.
</P>
<P>
Albright arrived here today for a three-day visit to Angola.
