<HEADLINE> S.Africa, China Sign Economic Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Two economic agreements
were signed between China and South Africa's Northern Cape
Province during a recent visit to China by provincial Premier
Manne Dipico, a local source said here today.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement issued by Dipico's office in
Kimberley, the premier and his provincial delegation feel pleased
with the nine-day visit, which began on January 5.
</P>
<P>
Two Chinese delegations are expected in Northern Cape to
evaluate business opportunities in the province, said the
statement.
</P>
<P>
One of the Chinese delegations will be from the Shanghai-based
China Feng Pu Group, which has signed an agreement with the South
African province for a housing project in Kimberley.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese company will send engineers to Northen Cape
Province for the production of modular houses.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Jinhai Geant Shoe Manufacturer has another agreement
with the South African province. The company will send its
representatives to South Africa for investment in the local shoe
making industry as soon as the project has been approved by
China's factory board.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the China Council for the Promotion of
International Trade and the Chinese People's Association for
Friendship are planning to send business delegations to Northern
Cape Province within the year to look into investment potential.
</P>
<P>
Dipico was accompanied by the provincial Economic Affairs
Minister, Goolam Akharwaray, Housing Affairs Minister Pakes
Dikgetsi and his advisor Dave Perkins during his visit to China.
</P>
</TEXT>
