<HEADLINE> Britain to Publish White Paper on Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The British government announced
today that it will publish a White Paper setting out its stance on
Europe ahead of the Inter-governmental Conference (IGC).
</P>
<P>
British Foreign Secretary Malcolm Rifkind is quoted by the BBC
television as saying the Paper would draw together strands of
policy on Europe, but it would not reveal the Government's hand
before the conference.
</P>
<P>
The IGC conference, due to be held in Italy in March, is aimed
at reviewing the operation of the Maastricht Treaty.
</P>
<P>
The move is seen as a significant victory for Euro-sceptic
Tories who are anxious to limit the Government's room in the
talks.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, leading Tory Euro-sceptic Bill Cash has welcomed the
Gvernment's decision to publish the White Paper, saying the move
would "remove a great deal of uncertainty" about its European
policy.
</P>
<P>
Bill Walker MP is quoted as saying that he was delighted
lawmakers would get the chance to debate the White Paper and put
their views on the IGC conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
