<HEADLINE> Soeharto Calls for Rice Self-Sufficiency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Soeharto
here today called on all farmers to maintain rice self-sufficiency
in the country.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks after presenting awards to farmers and
local officials who have succeeded in implementing the rice
self-sufficiency program.
</P>
<P>
Since rice production is still prone to natural disasters, said
the president, the progress in development process also presents
new challenges.
</P>
<P>
On efforts to increase food production, Soeharto said that it
is not only aimed to meet the demand of the people but also to
increase the income of the farmers.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian head of state also stressed the importance of
improving the skills of farmers.
</P>
<P>
"The success of agricultural development is determined by the
farmers' skills. So, they should learn and master effective
technology," he said.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia, once the biggest rice importing country in the
world, became rice-sufficiency in 1984.  
</P>
</TEXT>
