<HEADLINE> U.S. Astronaut Speaks To S.African Children From Outer Space </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 18 (Xinhua)-- United States astronaut
Winston Scott today spoke to a group of 40 South African school
children from the space shuttle "Endeavour".
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the office of South African Minister of
Arts, Culture, Science and Technology said that live discussion
was held at a South African Broadcasting Corporation studio in
Aucklandpark of Johannesburg. Minister Ben Ngubane also attended
the discussion.
