<HEADLINE> Four Killed in Apartment House Fire in US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Flames raged through an
apartment building in Chicago early today, killing at least four
people and injuring more than 40 others.
</P>
<P>
The fire, started shortly after 3:00 a.m. in a fifth-floor
apartment, forced some panicked occupants to leap from upper
stories of the eight-story Lake Grove Village apartment building
on Chicago's South Side.
</P>
<P>
Fire fighters arrived in time to rescue about 60 people from
the burning building.
</P>
<P>
The fire was brought under control in about 90 minutes, but the
cause was still under investigation. Officials believed that the
blaze might have been caused by careless use of smoking materials.
</P>
