<HEADLINE> Lesotho King Moshoeshoe's Successor Announced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Crown Prince David Mahato
Bereng Seeiso of Lesotho was named by the country's college of
chiefs in Maseru today as successor to his father, the late King
Moshoeshoe II.
</P>
<P>
However, according to South African Broadcasting Corporation
radio news, no date for the inauguration of the future head of
state has been set and his mother, Queen Mamohato, is still
acting as regent.
</P>
<P>
The 32-year-old Mahato, the elder of King Moshoeshoe II's
sons, ruled as King Letsie III from November 1990 to January 1995
while his father was in exile in England.
</P>
<P>
King Moshoeshoe II was killed in a car accident Monday morning
in the Maluti Mountains when his car veered off the road and went
down the hillside.
</P>
<P>
Moshoeshoe II would be buried on January 26 at the top of
Thaba Bosiu, the Basotho National Shrine near Maseru. 
</P>
</TEXT>
