<HEADLINE> Xi'an-Baoji Expressway Going into Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The 155-km-long Xi'an-Baoji
Expressway opened to traffic today, shortening the traveling time
from this capital city of Shaanxi Province to Baoji, Shaanxi's
leading industrial city, from four hours to two.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua, also a member of the Political Bureau
of the Chinese Communist Party's Central Committee, was present at
the ribbon-cutting ceremony which inaugurated this longest
expressway in northwest China.
</P>
<P>
The expressway, costing more than 1.2 billion yuan, has a
designed speed of 100 kph and a flow capacity of 25,000 vehicles
per day.
</P>
<P>
The trial use of the highway started in December 5, 1995.
</P>
