<HEADLINE> hke --Algeria Rose Atop in Group B </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Algeria scored two
unanswered goals to beat Sierra Leone in a Group B match of the
African Nation's Cup soccer tournament at Bloemfontein, South
Africa, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Striker Ali Mecabih was the hero of the match as he took the
limelight with two goals at the 41st and 63rd minutes
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The win put Algeria to the top of the group with 4 points.
The Algerian eleven drew with Zambia in their first match at the
tournament.
</P>
<P>
Following are the team standings of Group B after Thursday's
match (tabulated under matches played, won, drawn, lost, goals
for, against, points):
</P>
<P>
Algeria 2 1 1 0 2 0 4
</P>
<P>
Sierra Leone  2 1 0 1 2 3 3
</P>
<P>
Zambia  1 0 1 0 0 0 1
</P>
<P>
Burkina Faso  1 0 0 1 1 2 0
</P>
