<HEADLINE> Stocks, Dollar Fall in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices fell back on selling
by domestic institutions in Tokyo today and the dollar lost steam
against the yen on position-adjustment selling after a surge to a
22-month high Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues closed at
20,370.04, down 200.22 points, or 0.97 percent, from Wednesday's
close.
</P>
<P>
The Tokyo Stock Price Index, covering all first-section shares
of the Tokyo Stock Exchange, dropped 17.70 points, or 1.10
percent, to 1,587.31.
</P>
<P>
On today's Tokyo Foreign Exchange, the dollar was quoted at
105.31-33 yen at 5 p.m., down from 105.55-60 yen at 9 a.m. It
traded in a narrow range of 105.31-70 yen during the day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
