<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Air Cargo Hits Record High In 1995 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The total volume of cargo
handled by Hong Kong Air Cargo Terminals Limited (HACTL) at Kai
Tak Airport registered an 11 percent increase in 1995, a slow year
for the region's economy.
</P>
<P>
The HACTL handled 1.397 million tons of air cargo last year,
recording a significant growth over the 1994's total of 1.25
million tons.
</P>
<P>
Exports climbed 10.8 percent to 660,000 tons, imports jumped by
12.5 percent to 560,000 tons, and transshipments grew by 11.5
percent to 170,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The HACTL has decided to invest one billion US dollars to build
the world largest air cargo handling complex at Chek Lap Kok,
which will be capable of dealing 2.6 million tons a year when
starting operation in mid-1998.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
