<HEADLINE> 15 Indonesians Killed in Trainer Aircraft Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen Indonesians including a
trainer aircraft pilot and three trainee pilots were killed in a
trainer aircraft accident today in Bandung, capital of West Java
province.
</P>
<P>
The trainer aircraft crashed and hit four shops in a downtown
street named Jalan Jamaika this noon.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft owned by the Curug Aviation Education and Training
Center exploded, setting four shops on fire, according to reports
reaching here this evening quoting some witnesses.
</P>
<P>
The witnesses said the trainer was in a slanting position
before finally crashing to the ground and exploding, burning two
cars, two motorbikes and a pedicab.
</P>
<P>
An Antara report said that the pilot reportedly informed the
air force base that the plane was having engine trouble while
flying at an altitude of 500 feet.
</P>
<P>
Investigation on the exact cause of the crash will be carried
out later.  
</P>
</TEXT>
