<HEADLINE> Beijing's New Railway Station to Open Sunday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The new West Beijing Railway
Station, the largest, most expensive and most technically advanced
in China, is scheduled to go into operation this Sunday.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, the very first day of operation, a total of 31 pairs
of passenger trains will leave or arrive at the new station, which
serves as the northern terminus of the Beijing-Kowloon (Hong Kong)
Railway.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhu Jialu, one of the architects of the station,
it was built on a 51-ha tract of land, at a cost of of over six
billion yuan (about 714.3 million US dollars). It is designed to
handle 60 to 90 passenger trains and 250,000 to 600,000 passengers
a day.
</P>
<P>
The new station, located in southwestern Beijing, has a floor
space of 500,000 sq m, 10 times the size of the present Beijing
Railway Station. Its main building is 102 m high and 740 m
wide. Besides taking trains, booking tickets and sending baggage,
passengers can rest, shop, dine and be entertained there.
</P>
<P>
The new station has a 20,000-sq-m multi-function underground
hall, which also serves as the entrance to a subway station,
linking all checkpoints of the station for passengers'
convenience. It also has parking space for buses, cars, taxis and
bicycles.
</P>
<P>
Zhu noted that the new station absorbs natural light into its
main building through crystal glass, creating a bright and
comfortable environment for passengers.
</P>
<P>
Also, the station has applied more than 20 items of new
technology, including a computerized control system, radio
communication and computerized ticketing and checkroom. The
tickets sold here are coded ones, containing details of the
departure station and destination, date and train number.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that construction work on the new station has
taken more than 20,000 workers three years thus far, and it will
not be fully operational until later this year.
</P>
<P>
Business people predict that the new station will become the
fourth commercial center in the capital city after the brisk
Xidan, Wangfujing and Qianmen areas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
