<HEADLINE> Car Accident Kills Four, Injures Hundred in North Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Four people were killed and more
than 100 injured, 40 seriously, in a disastrous pile-up on the
fog-bound Torino-Milano highway in north Italy on Wednesday, local
press reported.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 vehicles piled up on the foggy road 10
kilometers outside Torino after a car crashed into a truck, triggering
a 10-hour traffic jam and a 6-kilometer-long queue of damaged cars.
</P>
<P>
Besides the bad weather which limited visibility, poor road
maintenance is being blamed for the fatal accident on the highway
built in 1929, said local police investigating the crash. 
</P>
</TEXT>
