<HEADLINE> Spain Provides 900 Million Dollar Loan to Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Spain has agreed to grant a
loan of 900 million U.S. dollars to Algeria to finance trade deals
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed here today by Algerian Finance
Minister Bin Bitour and Spanish Minister of Commerce and Tourism
Javier Gomez Navarro.
</P>
<P>
According to the Algerian News Agency, 400 million dollars of
the loan will be earmarked for financing short-term trade deals,
another 400 million for medium-term deals, and the remaining 100
million to finance long-term social development projects.
</P>
<P>
The Spanish minister arrived in Algiers Tuesday on an official
visit to Algeria. 
</P>
