<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Hosts Seminar on Revision of Criminal Procedure Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 18 (Xinhua) -- the revisions of China's
Criminal Procedure Law will be of great help in cracking down on
crimes and protecting the citizens' rights and interests, a senior
Chinese lawmaker said here today.
</P>
<P>
Major revisions of the law will make a great contribution to
improving China's criminal procedure and judicial systems, said
Wang Hanbin, vice-chairman of the National People's Congress (NPC)
Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
Wang made the remark at a seminar on the draft amendments to
the Criminal Procedure Law.
</P>
<P>
The draft amendments have been made to the law over the past 17
years while drawing on advanced legislative experience in foreign
countries.
</P>
<P>
The revisions will further guarantee the interests of citizens
and enhance responsibility, co-operation and mutual supervision
among the country's law-enforcement organs, according to legal
experts.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was sponsored by the Law Committee and the
Committee for Internal and Judicial Affairs of the NPC, and the
Committee of Legislative Affairs of the NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
