<DOCNO> XIE19960118.0069 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-01-18 15:15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets Hong Kong Delegation (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Li Peng said that after 1997 there will not be a
superior-subordinate relationship between the mainland's
provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities and the
departments under the central government on the one side and the
Hong Kong SAR on the other.
</P>
<P>
The mainland's departments, provinces, autonomous regions and
municipalities will not interfere in affairs which come under the
jurisdiction of the Hong Kong SAR. This is clearly stipulated in
the Basic Law, he said.
</P>
<P>
After 1997, he said, their contacts and co-operation will be
conducted in accordance with the principle of "one country, two
systems" and the relevant stipulations of the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
The central government will strengthen its management in this
regard, he said, adding that the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs
Office of the State Council will exercise overall consideration
and co-ordination. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
