<DOCNO> XIE19960118.0070 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-01-18 15:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets Hong Kong Delegation (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Secondly, he said, in 1993 the Chinese government established
the Preliminary Working Committee for the Preparatory Committee of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, which has made
necessary preparations for the establishment of the Hong Kong SAR
and laid a good foundation for the work of the Preparatory
Committee.
</P>
<P>
Not long ago, he said, the NPC Standing Committee also
appointed members of the Preparatory Committee which has been
formed by fully taking into consideration factors and
representativeness of different quarters.
</P>
<P>
Now the work of the Preparatory Committee has entered the
stage of implementation, he said.
</P>
<P>
"I am sure that the Preparatory Committee will live up to
this heavy duty and play a more important role in implementing the
principle of 'one country, two systems'", he said.
</P>
<P>
Thirdly, he said, maintaining the political stability and
sustained economic growth on the Chinese mainland is also an
important condition and guarantee for the implementation of the
principle of "one country, two systems" as regards Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Li expressed the belief that, in accordance with the principle
of "one country, two systems", Hong Kong will practise capitalism
after July 1, 1997, and its residents' way for life will remain
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
This will be beneficial for Hong Kong's playing a better role
as an international financial, trade and shipping center, he
added.
</P>
