<HEADLINE> Five Duma Deputy Speakers Elected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Five deputy speakers of the
State Duma, the lower house of the Russian Parliament, were
elected today, new Duma Speaker Gennady Seleznyov confirmed.
</P>
<P>
Seleznyov, also chairman of the new Duma, said at his first
news conference that Alexander Shokhin, member of the "Our Home Is
Russia" bloc, became the first deputy speaker.
</P>
<P>
The other four deputy speakers elected are Svetlana Goryacheva
of the Communist Party of the Russian Federation, Mikhail
Gutsiriyev of the Liberal Democratic Party led by Vladimir
Zhirinovsky, Artur Chilingarov from the "Russian Regions" group
and Sergei Baburin from the "People's Power" group.
</P>
<P>
All the five were elected this morning by 359 votes for, 56
against and one abstention.
</P>
<P>
The Yabloko faction decided not to nominate its deputy speaker
candidate since its leader Grigory Yavlinsky reportedly objected
to having two communists in the Duma leadership.
</P>
<P>
Seleznyov is one of the leaders of the Communist Party.
</P>
<P>
However, Seleznyov said that one vacancy would be reserved for
the faction. One more deputy speaker is to be elected later, a
Duma source said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
