<HEADLINE> Li Lanqing Stresses Education on Jiangxi Inspection Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Li Lanqing called
for more reforms in educational undertakings to boost the ongoing
development of socialist market economy during a recent inspection
tour of east China's Jiangxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Li, also a member of the Political Bureau of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, urged on local officials
to manage the various types of schools well so as to carry out the
state's strategy of revitalizing the country with science and
education.
</P>
<P>
"The key way out for higher education is to rely on reform,"
the vice-premier said, noting that while there is a lack of funds
for higher education, redundant educational establishments have
led to poor efficiency.
</P>
<P>
"Only reforms can optimize and make full use of educational
sources, and as a result better educational efficiency can be
achieved," he said.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier pointed out that higher-learning institutions
subject to the departments of the central government should help
train large numbers of high-level talented personnel who will
serve local economic and social development.
</P>
<P>
Stressing the importance of teachers' colleges, Li asked local
officials to create a fine environment in which teachers are well
respected and education is paid great attention to.
</P>
<P>
During his inspection tour between January 15 and 18 in the
province, which used to be an old revolutionary base, Li went to
urban and rural educational institutions, taking with him the
regards of the central government.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier also heard reports from Jiangxi provincial
officials about the province's progress in the economic, social,
educational, commercial and foreign trade sectors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
