<HEADLINE> Algeria to Lift Curfew in Ramadan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The Algerian authorities
decided, for the first time in years, to lift the curfew imposed
on the capital city and nine other provinces for 30 days as from
the first day of the Moslem fasting holy month of Ramadan, said a
Interior Ministry statement released today.
</P>
<P>
The lifing will be maintained throughout Ramadan which will
begin on Sunday. The statement also called upon the inhabitants of
these provinces to remain vigilant and security-minded during
their movement at night, and to submit to surveillance by security
forces.
</P>
<P>
A state of curfew was imposed in Algiers and nine other
provinces ever since the outbreak of rioting incidents in January
1992, from 11 p.m. to 4.30 a.m.. 
</P>
</TEXT>
