<HEADLINE> Chechen Rebels Wiped Out in Dagestan Hostage Rescue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-six Russian soldiers were
killed and some 250 Chechen terrorists were wiped out in the
Kremlin mission to rescue 82 hostages held by Chechen
separatists in the southern Russian village of Pervomaiskoye.
</P>
<P>
Some 18 hostages are reported missing.
</P>
<P>
Russian President Boris Yeltsin said in the Kremlin today that
Russian forces had completed their operation against Chechen
rebels in the village near the border with Chechnya. The operation
to storm the village started on January 15.
</P>
<P>
The rebels had been trapped in the village for about a week
after trying to return to the breakaway republic with some 3,000
hostages captured on January 9 in the southern town of Kizlyar.
</P>
<P>
The incident triggered the second hostage crisis in seven
months involving Chechen rebels.
</P>
<P>
They were stopped the following day by Russian soldiers at
Pervomaiskoye on their way back home to Chechnya. Most of the
hostages were released, but the situation intensified as Russian
security forces entered the third day of battle to rescue the
remaining 100 or so hostages.
</P>
<P>
The Russian government vowed to punish the "bandits" but
promised not to risk the lives of the hostages.
</P>
<P>
In a gesture of support for their fellow rebels, a group of
Chechen fighters are still holding hostage a Russia-bound ship
with some 200 people on board near the Black Sea port of
Trabzon off the Turkish coast. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
