Myanmar Minister for Progress of Border Areas and National Races
and Development Affairs Lieutenant General Maung Thint, the report
added.
</P>
<P>
From January 5 up to 14, a total of 6,127 of the MTA members
had turned in to the government troops, bringing in 4,573 items of
arms and ammunition including small arms and heavy weapons,
according to the latest official statistics.  
