<HEADLINE> Chechens Try to Pierce Russian Lines Around Village </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Chechen rebels caught in a
hostage siege made several attempts to break out of the village
where they are being bombarded by Russian troops, Itar-Tass
News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Some of the guerillas finally managed to break out of
Pervomayskoye, a village in the Russian republic of Dagestan on
the Chechen border, at about 2:30 a.m.(local time). Injuries were
reported in the Russian forces.
</P>
<P>
Russian troops kept on shelling the village during the
overnight fighting and stopped the rebels for several hours, the
news media said, quoting Dagestan's Interior Ministry.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, about 300 fighters from Chechnya penetrated
the village of Sovetskoye near Pervomayskoye and tried to break
through an outer ring of Russian troops to rescue the trapped
rebels, the agency reported.
</P>
<P>
However, most of them were killed on the border and about 20
slipped back into Sovetskoye, but are being hunted by Russian
forces.
</P>
<P>
Two Russian soldiers were reported killed and two wounded in
the fighting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
