<HEADLINE> Beijing to Host International Elevator Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 18 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition of elevators and
related equipment will be held at the China International
Exhibition Center here from August 20 to 24 this year, the
organizers of the exhibition announced here today.
</P>
<P>
On display will be various types of elevators, escalators and
auxiliary components and testing devices. Relevant economic and
trade fairs and technological exchanges will also be held during
the five-day exhibition.
</P>
<P>
More than 70 elevator manufacturers from Germany, Italy, the
United States, Japan, the Republic of Korea, Chinese mainland as
well as Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan, and the world's major
elevator-related institutions, will be present at the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
China has become the world's third-largest elevator
manufacturer and the biggest elevator market. The 30,000 elevators
and escalators produced in China last year were not able to meet
the growing demand.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will be sponsored by the China Bidding Center for
Machinery and Electronics, the China Elevator Association and the
Beijing branch of the China Council for the Promotion of
International Trade. 
</P>
