<DATE_TIME> 1996-01-18 13:39 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada to Send Observers to Palestine Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Canada will send an 11-member
mission to observe the first general election to elect a
Palestinian government on January 20, Foreign Minister Andre
Ouellet said today.
</P>
<P>
"An international presence during the vote will contribute to
achieving a free and fair result which, in turn, will enhance the
long-term political stability of the region," he said.
</P>
<P>
Ouellet said the elections are a key element of the Middle
East peace process and constitute an important step in the
development of democracy for the Palestinians in the West Bank and
Gaza.
</P>
<P>
Canada is one of the ten countries and five international
organizations invited to observe the elections under the interim
Israeli-Palestinian agreement.
</P>
<P>
Some 676 candidates are battling for 88 seats on the new
Palestinian legislative council. 
</P>
</TEXT>
