<DATE_TIME> 1996-01-18 13:33 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Britain Will Join Single European Currency: Kinkel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 18 (Xinhua) -- German Foreign Minister Klaus
Kinkel said Wednesday that Britain will join the single European
currency in the end, unable to resist its tempting economic
advantages.
</P>
<P>
"Europe needs Britain and British contribution to the European
Union (EU) is indispensable," he told guests at the opening
ceremony for a European law center at Oxford University.
</P>
<P>
"It's better to catch the boat than swim after it," he said.
</P>
<P>
The German foreign minister also reaffirmed the German
government's commitment to federalist policies including a single
currency and common foreign, defense and security policies.
</P>
<P>
Kinkel called for a "fundamental" review of the working methods
of the EU commission at the forthcoming Inter-Governmental
Conference.
</P>
<P>
An opinion poll conducted by the Sunday Times late last year
showed 60 percent of respondents were opposed in principle to
British membership of a single European currency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
