<DATE_TIME> 1996-01-18 13:30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila Expedites Creation of East ASEAN Growth Fund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines is expediting
the creation of a 300 million US dollar growth fund for the
Brunei-Indonesia-Malaysia-Philippines - East ASEAN Growth Area
(BIMP-EAGA).
</P>
<P>
Finance Secretary Roberto de Ocampo today said that
consultations are being held between the private sector and the
government for the incorporation of the fund.
</P>
<P>
He said he hoped the growth fund will be launched by the fourth
quarter of the year.
</P>
<P>
The BIMP-EAGA growth fund is envisioned to be a catalyst for
the growth of the area.
</P>
<P>
It is supposed to be an investment fund for developmental and
commercial enterprises in the sub-region.
</P>
<P>
It is also supposed to be incorporated as a limited company
with an authorized capital of 300 million dollars and an initial
target capitalization of 180 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The mother fund of 180 million dollars would be contributed to
by Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia and the Philippines to the amount
of 30 million dollars each which would also be country sub-funds.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
