<DOCNO> XIE19960118.0107 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-01-18 13:23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua Spokesman on Supervision of Foreign Wire Services for Economic Information (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 18 (Xinhua) -- A spokesman for the Xinhua News
Agency made a speech here today expounding on some issues relating
to the agency's being authorized by the State Council to supervise
foreign wire services and their organs selling economic
information in China.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that the supervision is for the purpose of
establishing a standardized information market in China in the
course of building a socialist market economy, further
standardizing China's futures, securities and foreign currencies
information release system, promoting the development of an
orderly economic information market, and providing an environment
for equal competition among both Chinese and overseas
information organs.
</P>
<P>
The supervision will also help protect intellectual property of
foreign wire services and help domestic information organs protect
their own intellectual property, the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
It will better serve the opening-up policy, and not the other
way around, he said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the move is a normal one for a sovereign
state to exercise its sovereignty. Some Asian countries and a
number of other developing countries supervise the entry of
economic information from foreign wire services, he said, and
therefore it is also an international practice.
</P>
<P>
He said that Xinhua has experience in administering the foreign
wire services' recruitment of subscribers in China, and will
indubitably do a good job of managing the economic information
release by them and their economic information organs. He noted
that the move will affect neither the users' efficiency in
receiving the information nor the quality of technical services,
and the subscribers can go on getting information in a rapid and
comprehensive manner.
</P>
<P>
To ensure normal transition, he said, for a period of time, the
users' equipment and methods for receiving the information will
remain unchanged, and the technical services and equipment
installation will remain as they are. The technical means provided
by foreign wire services and their information organs will remain
in use at present in such on-line trading systems as financial
systems approved by Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
What Xinhua will do is to apply synchronic examination of the
economic information released by the wire services and their
information organs, instead of examining the information before it
is released, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Of course, if contents which slander China and jeopardize
China's national interests are found, Xinhua, with departments
concerned, will deal with it," he noted.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
