<HEADLINE> Mozambican Govt Urged To Fight Terrorist Acts Of Zimbabwean Dissidents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The Mozambican government
should take measures to crack down on the terrorist acts of
Zimbabwean dissidents operating in Mozambique in order to
safeguard the country's sovereignty, a senior Mozambican official
said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaker of Parliament Eduardo Mulembwe was reacting to the
mounting armed attacks by Zimbabwean dissidents on coaches and
passengers in Sofala Province. The Zimbabweans committed two
attacks on travelling vehicles on the No.I Highway last week,in
which two people were killed and three others wounded.
</P>
<P>
These criminal activities have posed a threat to peace and
stability in Mozambique, Mulembwe said.
</P>
<P>
The Zimbabwean dissidents, who are reportedly members of
ZANU-Ndonga led by Ndabaningi Sithole, infiltrated into
Mozambique's Manica Province and camped there a few years ago.
They often slip back into Zimbabwe to carry out subversive
activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
