<HEADLINE> ADB Finances Flood Control Project in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
today approved loans totaling 90 million US dollars to Indonesia
for the North Java flood control project.
</P>
<P>
The main objective of the project is to improve the quality of
life for the rural and urban populations in flood-affected areas
along 400 kilometers of the north coast of Java in the provinces
of West and Central Java.
</P>
<P>
The project will also promote sound management of natural
resources and the environment in the country.  
</P>
