<HEADLINE> ADB Funds Port Project in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
today approved a loan of 52 million US dollars to China for the
Fangcheng port project in the southwestern part of China.
</P>
<P>
The objective of the project is to build a one-berth container
terminal, a one-berth bulk-cargo terminal and a 20-kilometer
highway to the port.
</P>
<P>
