<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sales of 21 Leading Industries Up in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Sales of 21 key industries in
the Philippines reached 299.8 billion pesos (11.99 billion US
dollars) in the first 10 months of 1995, up 14 percent from 262.6
billion pesos (10.50 billion dollars) in the same period of 1994.
</P>
<P>
The Department of Trade and Industry today traced the sales
upswing to an increasing propensity to buy, a direct result of
improved incomes.
</P>
<P>
Top gainers in terms of sales value and volume include pulp and
paper, plastics, cars, electronics, agriculture, chemicals and
metallic mining.
</P>
<P>
Net sales of pulp and paper products amounted to 7.5 billion
pesos (300 million dollars), up 46 percent from the year-ago total
of 5.1 billion pesos (204 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, low demand caused sales of sugar, textile, wooden
furniture and garments to fall during the period.  
</P>
</TEXT>
