<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Subic Creates More Jobs and Exports More Goods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The Subic free port, the former
US Navy base, has already generated more than 36,000 jobs, almost
double the number offered by the US Navy when it had its base
there.
</P>
<P>
According to a report by Richard Gordon, chairman of the Subic
Bay Metropolitan Authority, of the 36,000 jobs created, 18,450 are
direct hires or regular employees, compared with 13,000 direct
hires or regular employees offered by the US Navy.
</P>
<P>
Also, Gordon reported that export from Subic leaped from 19
million US dollars in 1994 to 169 million US dollars in last year,
accounting for 4 percent of the national export value of 14.3
billion US dollars in 1995.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
