<HEADLINE> Police Release Hostages From Terrorist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Russian police rescued 28
hostages on a bus from a terrorist near the western Siberian city
of Surgut last night, according to the Itar-Tass News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The 28 local workers were taken hostage when going home from
work on a bus last night.
</P>
<P>
The terrorist hijacked the bus to an airport and attempted to
bring six of the hostages to fly with him to Pervomaiskoye, the
Dagestan village where Chechen guerrillas are holding out against
Russian forces.
</P>
<P>
Interior Ministry special forces stormed the bus at the airport
and shot the hostage-taker, who later died in the hospital. One
hostage was hurt in the fight.
</P>
<P>
The terrorist, aged 25, has not been identified yet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
