<HEADLINE> Trainer Aircraft Crashes in Bandung, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- One trainer aircraft crashed
today on a sideway in Bandung downtown, capital of west Java,
Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Right after taking off from Bandung's husein sastranegara, the
trainer aircraft at local time 11:30 a.m. crashed onto the
Sudirman street, the busiest section of the city.
</P>
<P>
It is still unclear on the cause of the crash and any
casualties in the accident.  
</P>
</TEXT>
