<HEADLINE> HK Labor Earnings on Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's average labor
earnings in all major sectors of the economy recorded an increase
of 11.7 percent in nominal terms in the third quarter of 1995
compared with a year earlier, according to official date released
today.
</P>
<P>
After discounting changes in consumer prices, there was an
increase of 2.9 percent in real terms, statistics of the Census
and Statistics Department showed.
</P>
<P>
All major sectors surveyed recorded increases in average labor
earnings both in nominal terms and real terms.
</P>
<P>
The average payroll per person engaged in the manufacturing
sector recorded the largest increase, by 12.9 percent in nominal
terms or four percent in real terms in the third quarter of 1995
compared with the same period of 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
