<HEADLINE> Fifth Informal Meeting between Chinese Officials, HK Civil Servants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese government officials
and senior Hong Kong civil servants ended their fifth informal
get-together here today.
</P>
<P>
Yuan Pengyan, secretary-general of the Xinhua News Agency HK
Branch, told a press briefing after the meeting that the four-hour
 get-together was as successful as the previous four.
</P>
<P>
He said that not long ago the foreign ministers of China and
Britain reviewed the previous four meetings with satisfaction, and
 expressed the hope that such meetings will continue in a smooth
way.
</P>
<P>
He said the two foreign ministers have reached a common view on
 cooperation between the Hong Kong government and the Preparatory
Committee of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR),
which is to be established soon.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that in the remaining more than 500 days Hong Kong
civil servants will surely be able to do their job well," Yuan
said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that Hong Kong civil servants will make
continued efforts in maintaining the normal functioning of the
Hong Kong government, cooperating with the Preparatory Committee,
creating favorable conditions for the smooth transition of Hong
Kong and for the organization of the SAR government, acquainting
themselves with the Basic Law and the conditions of China, as well
 as learning Putonghua and the Chinese language.
</P>
<P>
Eight Chinese government officials and five senior Hong Kong
civil servants participated in today's meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
