<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arafat Visits Jordan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat
today paid a short visit to the kingdom to brief Jordanian
officials on the forthcoming Palestinian elections.
</P>
<P>
Jordan's Prime Minister Sharif Zeid Ben Shaker held talks with
Arafat on bilateral relations and the latest developments of
Palestinian negotiations with Israel as well as the preparation
for the Palestinian elections, Radio Jordan said.
</P>
<P>
Arafat, chairman of the Palestine Liberation Organization
(PLO), said after the talks that he briefed the prime minister on
his talks with U.S. Vice President Al Gore Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Arafat, who is on his first visit to the Kingdom this year,
said the forthcoming elections are very important as it is the
first elections on the Palestinian territories.
</P>
<P>
He said the second phase of the negotiations between Israel
and the Palestinian National Authority (PNA) would focus on the
status of Jerusalem, the issues of refugee and Jewish settlement
as well as the final border between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Arafat promised that the elections will be held in a brotherly
and fair-play spirit.
</P>
<P>
Arafat's visit was widely seen as part of his campaign to gain
support from the Arab countries ahead of the scheduled elections.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
