<DATE_TIME> 1996-01-18 10:59 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao to Hold Bullfights for Lunar New Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Macao will hold bullfights to
entertain local citizens to celebrate the coming Chinese lunar New
Year, organizers said today.
</P>
<P>
The Portuguese style of bullfights will be held between
February 17 and 25. A bullfighting team of 55 people, including
four bullfighters on horseback and 24 bull-catchers, and a total
of 40 bulls and six horses will come from Portugal.
</P>
<P>
Six bullfighting shows, each scheduled to last some two and
half hours, will be staged during the holidays, said Jose Pinto,
manager of the "Taurus" Company, an organizer of the activities.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the Macao Government Tourist Office expressed the
hope that the event would help boost tourism, which is the pillar
industry of the local economy.
</P>
<P>
Portuguese bullfighting was said to have started in the 12th
century. But unlike Spanish bullfighting, bulls in the fighting
are not killed in the arena.
</P>
<P>
Similar activities were held in Macao over 20 years ago. A
large number of people, mostly from Hong Kong, came to watch the
event.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
