<DATE_TIME> 1996-01-18 10:58 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Scientific Research Activities Urged in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Education
Minister Najib Tun Razak today urged the government to step up the
level of research activities.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference here today, Najib said at
present, Malaysia's financial allocations for research work
accounted for less than two percent of its gross domestic product
(GDP). Efforts must be made to increase the research fund to five
percent of the GDP, he added.
</P>
<P>
Najib said his ministry would grant 100,000 Malaysian Ringgit
(about 40,000 US dollars) to each local university beginning from
this year to carry out the research work.
</P>
<P>
In an effort to step up research activities, Najib said, his
ministry was also trying to increase the number of graduates
pursuing their education to master's level to 20 percent from 10
or 11 percent currently.
</P>
<P>
Besides that, efforts were also being made to increase the
number of master degree and Ph.D. degree holders, he said.
</P>
<P>
Owing to its rapid economic development, Malaysia now needs
more professional personnel in its economic activities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
