<HEADLINE> Gaddafi to Meet Mubarak in Cairo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi is
to arrive here today for a one-day visit to Egypt to meet with
President Hosni Mubarak.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders are expected to discuss bilateral relations,
the latest developments of the Libya-West crisis and a number of
other issues of mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations imposed air, arms and diplomatic embargo on
Libya in April 1992 after Libya refused to succumb to a western
demand for extraditing two Libyan nationals, who were suspected of
bombing a Pan Am passenger plane over Lockerbie, Scotland, in
1988, in which 270 people were killed.
</P>
<P>
The United States and Britain insist that the suspects be tried
in the U.S. or Britain while Libya insists that they be tried in
a neutral country or in the International Court of Justice in the
Hague.
</P>
<P>
According to local press reports, Gaddafi will also brief
Mubarak on the current situation in the Arab Maghreb Union (AMU)
and the ongoing efforts to contain the present crisis between Algeria
and Morocco in the wake of the latter's decision to freeze its
membership in the AMU.
</P>
<P>
The Arab Maghreb Union groups Algeria, Libya, Mauritania,
Morocco and Tunisia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
