<HEADLINE> UN Envoy to Afghanistan Leaves for Kabul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 18 (Xinhua) -- UN special envoy to
Afghanistan Mehmud Mestiri left here today for Kabul to meet
Afghan President Burhanuddin Rabbani.
</P>
<P>
Mestiri will also hold talks with Rabbani's top commander Ahmad
Masood who proposed a new peace formula to Afghan opposition
groups last week.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban and the three-party opposition alliance rejected
Masood's proposal that called for a cease-fire, opening of
highways, exchange of POWs and dialogues.
</P>
<P>
Before his departure to Kabul, Mestiri Wednesday visited
Jalalabad in east Afghanistan and met Governor of Afghan Nangahar
Province Haji Abdul Qadeer.
</P>
<P>
He also exchanged views with Pakistani President Farooq Leghari
and Prime Minister Benazir Bhutto on restoring peace in the
war-torn Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Mestiri, who arrived here last Friday to revive the UN peace
mission in Afghanistan, had to put off his planned trip to Kabul
on Sunday due to a heavy snowfall in the Afghan capital.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that this time he had prepared two name-lists for
an interim council which would take power from Rabbani.
</P>
<P>
He said that he would hold discussions with all Afghan parties
on the establishment of the future Afghan government and
restoration of peace in the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
