<HEADLINE> Juventus Wins Italian Super Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Juventus defeated Parma 1-0 in
Turin, Italy on Wednesday to win the Italian Super Cup title for
the first time, despite playing the second half with 10 men.
</P>
<P>
The winning goal came in the 32nd minute as Vialli tucked the
ball home after Alessandro del Piero delivered a pass to Italian
international Fabrizio Ravanelli.
</P>
<P>
In the 40th minute when the Juventus goalkeeper Angelo Perruzzi
was sent off after a clash with Parma's Bulgarian striker Hristo
Stoichkov, del Piero had to came off to make way for the reserve
goalkeeper Michelangelo Rampulla.
</P>
<P>
The Cup was set up eight years ago for a clash between league
champions and Italian Cup winners. 
