<HEADLINE> Shanghai Industrial Spraw </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Industrial centers in this
large city are spreading into suburban areas to match the local
economic development.
</P>
<P>
The Baoshan District, at the juncture of the urban district and
rural areas, is considered an ideal place for investment because
it is only eight km from the city proper.
</P>
<P>
A new industrial park was built in Qilian Township, southwest
of Baoshan, recently. Infrastructure that includes transformers,
waterworks, and gas service has been completed, at a total cost of
54 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
This has attracted 10 large and medium-sized projects with a
combined investment of 8.3 billion yuan resulting in agreements
with a dozen key enterprises, including the Shanghai Plane Engine
Plant and No.11 Chemical Fiber Mill. 
