<HEADLINE> Australian Stock Market Steady </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- The Australian stock market
remained steady today despite a downturn in the Wall Street
overnight and uncertainty in the gold price.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index nudged up by 0.1 points to 2250.4
points.
</P>
<P>
Local dealers said that the Australian stock market maintained
its gains in the past few days despite that the Dow Jones
industrial average fell 21.32 points to 5066.9 points last night.
</P>
<P>
They said that the local bourse was supported by overseas
interest in Australian bank shares.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index added 2.6 points to 3387.6 points,
while the all resources index lost 1.8 points to close at 1390.5
points.
</P>
<P>
The Gold price surged above 400 US dollars per fine ounce in
Sydney during the day but closed at 399.5 US dollars per ounce.
</P>
<P>
There is still uncertainty whether the gold price will go up or
down in overseas markets tonight.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totalled 287 million shares, valued at 546
million Australian dollars (404.04 million US dollars).  
</P>
