<HEADLINE> Cold Forces Lim out of Japan Open Badminton </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 18 (Xinhua) -- An influenza has forced world
number four Swede Lim Xiaoqing out of the contention for the
women's singles title at Japan Badminton Open here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Lim, a 28-year-old born in China, had upset Indonesia's Olympic
gold medalist Susi Susanti on her way to the All-England title
last season and was listed as the third seed here.
</P>
<P>
Her second-round opponent Debra Oconnor of Trinidad and Tobago
automatically entered the next round.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, China's five women in the singles event, four of
them with seedings here, all went through easily.
</P>
<P>
World champion Ye Zhaoying and sixth seed Han Jingna all moved
into the next round without lifting their rackets as their
respective opponent pulled out of the event.
</P>
<P>
Fifth seed Wang Chen swept past Jeng Shwu-jen of Chinese
Taipei, seventh seed Zhang Ning nipped Japanese Sachiko Sekimoto,
while unseeded Yao Yan rolled over another Japanese Chikako
Nakayama, all with straight sets.
</P>
<P>
There were no upsets with other seeds, including defending
champion Susanti, Camilla Martin of Denmark and Lidya
Djaelawidjaya of Indonesia. 
