<HEADLINE> Fujian Reports Good Grain Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Southeast China's Fujian
Province, which is short of arable lands, has reported a record
grain harvest last year thanks to introducing scientific farming
technique and investing more in this field.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, Fujian grew 2.02 million hectares of
grain last year, up 15,000 hectares over the previous year, and
reaped 9.2 million tons of grain, up 325,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
To boost the grain output in Fujian with only 0.038 hectares
per capita, the provincial government has aroused the enthusiasm
of farmers in grain production while allocating 30 million yuan a
year to aid the construction of market-oriented grain production
bases, adopting effective measures to protect farmland, and
boosting per unit grain output by relying on science.
</P>
<P>
In addition, banks grant an annual of 100 million yuan in
loans to rural areas. 
</P>
