<HEADLINE> Fujian Reports Fiscal Surplus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, January 18 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province
reported a fiscal surplus of nearly 800 million yuan (about 96
million US dollars) in 1995, according to official statistics
released here today.
</P>
<P>
The statistics show that the province's fiscal revenue rose 30
percent last year to 18 billion yuan while the provincial
expenditure was up 3.5 billion yuan to 17.2 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The 1995 revenue was also six times that of 1985, when Fujian
ceased to be reliant on State subsidies and started to contribute
to the national treasury.
</P>
<P>
Officials and analysts say that Fujian's fiscal balance is a
result of rapid and healthy development of the local economy. The
province's gross domestic product was more than 220 billion yuan
last year.
</P>
<P>
Fujian's total exports reached nine billion US dollars and
foreign investment in the Chinese province was worth four billion
US dollars last year.  
</P>
