<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Anhui Develops Hi-Tech Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, January 18 (Xinhua) -- A high technology research and
development center is taking shape in east China's Anhui Province,
a major science-education base in the country.
</P>
<P>
The center will place emphasis on developing 16 new and hi-tech
projects which are expected to yield an additional output value of
30 billion yuan over the next five years with the assistance of
some major universities.
</P>
<P>
It has made a breakthrough in research in new materials,
micro-electronics, information science, and the application of
electronics to machine building and bio-engineering.
</P>
<P>
There is a vast possibility for the comprehensive use of
alumite and the development of digitally-controlled household
appliances and machine tools, automatic fire alarms, laser
processing equipment, and new types of sensors.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government will invest more in hi-tech
development, and has called for closer cooperation among research
bodies, institutes of higher learning, and enterprises and improve
technical markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
