<HEADLINE> Agassi Fined for Audible Obscenity in Autralian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- World number two Andre Agassi
of the United States was fined 1,500 U.S. dollars Thursday for
swearing in an Australian Tennis Open match in Melbourne,
Australia.
</P>
<P>
Agassi, also the number two seed here, vented his frustration
with audible obscenities after hitting a long shot out of the
court during a second-round match against compatriot Vince Spadea
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Agassi was given a code violation by Gerry Armstrong, the chair
umpire of the match, which he won 6-4, 6-2 and 6-3.
</P>
<P>
He meets another American Steve Bryan in the third round.
</P>
