<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eleven Months of Rapid Tourism Development in 1995 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 18 (Xinhua) -- The latest statistics show
that China had earned 7.98 billion US dollars from overseas
tourism through November of last year, up 18.26 percent over the
same 1994 period.
</P>
<P>
China had hosted 42.13 million overseas tourists in the
11-month period, a 5.61 percent rise, and travel services in the
country handled 7.43 million people in tour groups, up 4.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Of the 15 major sources, the Republic of Korea scored the
biggest leap in the number of visitors to China during the period,
reaching 52.5 percent. The increase for the Philippines was 21.2
percent, and that of Japan, Singapore, Malaysia, Germany,
Australia, and Canada rose by more than ten percent each.
</P>
<P>
In November of last year, China received 3.8 million overseas
tourists, up 1.51 percent over the same period of the previous
year, bringing in 397 million US dollars in tourism income.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
