<HEADLINE> Tourism Grows 20 Percent Annually In Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Tourism is one the fastest
growing sector in Uganda's economy, with an annual average growth
rate of 20 percent, the local daily "the New Vision" reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted the Uganda Tourist Board Chairman, Peter
Kamya, as saying that the number of tourists coming to Uganda had
out-stripped all projections.
</P>
<P>
A yearly inflow of 144,000 tourists by the year 2000 had been
projected, he said, adding that by 1995, the figure had been
surpassed and in 1994 the board registered an inflow of over
149,000 tourists.
</P>
<P>
Kamya attributed the success to the existing peace and
stability prevailing across the country.
</P>
<P>
Other reasons for the success are the conducive climate,
spectacular landscapes and varied wildlife in the country,
he said. 
</P>
