<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hangzhou Successful in Banning Use of Styrofoam Boxes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Hangzhou, the provincial
capital of Zhejiang Province, has been successful in banning the
use of styrofoam fast food boxes.
</P>
<P>
Paper food boxes have been used since September of last year to
replace the styrofoam ones, which are difficult to dispose of.
</P>
<P>
Hangzhou is the first city in China to outlaw the use of
styrofoam boxes. It is a famous tourist attraction that is known
as the "Heavenly Paradise".
</P>
<P>
In the past, about 200,000 styrofoam fast food boxes were used
every day in the city, accounting for 40 percent of the city's
plastic waste materials.
</P>
<P>
Unfortunately, it takes about 500 years for styrofoam to
decompose. According to public health officials, Hangzhou will
continue efforts to look for environmentally-friendly substitutes
for plastic packaging materials and agricultural-use plastic
sheeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
