<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 18 (Xinhua) -- An outbreak of rioting
occurred early today at Kuala Lumpur's Sungai Besi Refugee Camp
where some 4,000 Vietnamese refugees are awaiting repatriation.
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred during a routing inspection of the camp
by police personnel, officials said.
</P>
<P>
One residential block was set on fire by the inmates who also
threw stones during the riot, they said.
</P>
<P>
It also said these refugees were protesting against the move to
send them back to their country.
</P>
<P>
A fire engine could be seen outside the camp's fence and the
smoke of the burning block could be seen far outside the camp.
</P>
<P>
Officials said the situation was now under control and a
representative from the United Nations High Commissioner for
Refugees entered the camp at about 10 a.m. today.
</P>
<P>
According to Malaysia's national news agency Bernama, On June
5, 1995, more than 4,000 refugees broke out of the camp and police
were forced to use tear gas and powerful jets of water to force
them back into the camp. 
</P>
