<HEADLINE> Commander of Black Sea Fleet Removed from Post </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, January 17 (Xinhua) -- The commander of the Black Sea
Fleet, Eduart Baltin, has been removed from his post, the press
center of the fleet announced here today.
</P>
<P>
His removal reportedly complies with an agreement signed
between Russian President Boris Yeltsin and Ukrainian President
Leonid Kuchma, who visited Russia on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that Baltin was removed because of his strong
attitude over the Black Sea Fleet, which was commanded and manned
mostly by Russians but based in independent Ukraine after the
breakup of the Soviet Union.
</P>
<P>
Baltin's attitude became the main factor hindering the
solution of problems between Russia and Ukraine over the Black Sea
Fleet, according to reports.
</P>
<P>
Years of negotiations have brought agreements under which
Russian owns half the fleet outright and rents another quarter
from Ukraine, giving Russia 669 of the fleet's aging ships and the
Ukrainian navy 164. 
</P>
</TEXT>
