the participation of its enterprises at commercial fairs in Latin
American countries this year to seek more trade opportunities.
</P>
<P>
The country has signed trade accords with Venezuela, Brazil,
Peru, Mexico and Colombia in an effort to reverse the fall in
trade with these traditional trade partners.
</P>
<P>
Trade between the Czech Republic and Latin American countries
totaled 353 million U.S. dollars in January-November 1995,
accounting for only one percent of the country's foreign trade.
</P>
