<HEADLINE> Experts to Prepare First American Summit On Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTA FE DE BOGOTA, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Experts from 22
American countries will meet Monday and Tuesday in Colombia to
make preparations for the first hemispherical summit on science
and technology.
</P>
<P>
The experts will discuss the drafts of six issues which were
entrusted to the governments of Brazil, Jamaica, Venezuela, Chile,
Colombia, the United States and Honduras.
</P>
<P>
They include the exchange of experience in technological
cooperation, the relation between science and technology and
applications, the financing of science and technology development
programs and the establishment of mechanisms for the full
participation of relatively least-developed countries.
</P>
<P>
The upcoming summit was called by the heads of state or
government who participated in the Summit of the Americas held in
Miami, the U.S., in December 1994 and the first hemispherical
summit will be attended by ministers of science and technology of
the countries concerned.
</P>
<P>
It will also be attended by delegates from the Organization of
American States, the Inter-American Development Bank and the
Common Market of Scientific and Technological Knowhow.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that the meeting could contribute to the
strengthening of the regional economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
