<HEADLINE> Brazil's Economic News Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Following are some
economic news briefs about Brazil:
</P>
<P>
Sales of Foreign Automobiles Hit Record
</P>
<P>
Brazilian automobile importers reported unprecedented sales in
1995, with 119,543 imported vehicles sold in the domestic market,
an increase of 53.4 percent over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
When the products of local assembly plants are included, the
total number of foreign automobiles sold in the country last year
amounted to 368,136 units.
</P>
<P>
Renault was the leader in the Brazilian market with 19,877
vehicles sold. The French car giant was followed by Sudcoreana
Asia (11,342), KIA (11,208) and Toyota (9,047).
</P>
<P>
Chicken Production, Consumption Increase
</P>
<P>
Brazil reported a record chicken production of four million
tons in 1995, with the per capita consumption reaching 20
kilograms.
</P>
<P>
The country's poultry production has soared 170 percent in the
past 10 years with a yearly increase of 8 percent, while the per
capita consumption jumped from five kilograms 20 years ago.
</P>
</TEXT>
