<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hangzhou Residents Support Charity (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Orphans and disabled children are not the only ones benefitting
from Hangzhou residents.
</P>
<P>
In 1994 a local newspaper reported that Zhao Qiangying, a
uremia patient in critical condition, could not afford an
operation that could possibly save her life. Local residents
donated 63,000 yuan to her within one week.
</P>
<P>
According to Ma Shiyong, president of the Hangzhou Charitable
Society and deputy Hangzhou mayor, the charity undertaking is
intended to help childless senior residents, orphans, deserted
infants, families living under the poverty line and other people
in financial difficulty.
</P>
<P>
Hangzhou's social welfare institutes, homes for the aged,
children's welfare institutes, and factories run by welfare
organizations have helped a large number of the needy people, Ma
said.
</P>
<P>
He said the local social welfare system is now taking care of
the childless old people, raising orphans, helping the disabled,
aiding the poor and assisting those in financial difficulty.
</P>
<P>
All sectors of society are being encouraged to carry forward
humanitarianism and give more assistance to those people, he said.
</P>
<P>
While preparing for its establishment, the Hangzhou Charitable
Society opened ten charity bazaars, and organized benefit
performances and donation collection.
</P>
<P>
Within one year, 71 enterprises and institutions and thousands
of individuals contributed money and materials totaling 4.27
million yuan, Mao said.
</P>
<P>
The Hangzhou-based Chunsili Cosmetics Company donated 60,000
yuan to the society. "Enterprises should help those in financial
difficulty. Only a society full of compassion is a fine one," the
company Manager Jin Guifu said.
</P>
<P>
So far, the Hangzhou City Charitable Society has sent 380,000
yuan worth-of tonics, washing machines and pianos to the
Children's Welfare Institute, the Social Welfare Institute and
low-income families, Mao said.
</P>
<P>
Ma said that the society plans to spend 20 million yuan
building a charity center in Hangzhou. The center will have such
facilities as a 200-bed apartment building for senior residents, a
50-bed charity hospital and a charity service agency to provide
professional training and advise to the disabled and low-income
people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
