<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Barcelona jumped to the top of
Group B at the European Champion Clubs basketball semifinal series
after beating Real Madrid 94-82 in an all-Spain clash on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Barcelona now leads Group B with 17 points, one ahead of
Real. Panathinaikos of Greece stands third with 15 points and has
one more game to play on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Barcelona, paced by international Arturas Karnisovas hit 29
points, took control after the beginning of the match and opened a
12-3 lead with a series of triples.
</P>
<P>
Champions Real fought back after American forward Joe
Arlauckaus found himself and began to combine well with guard
Pablo Laso, to bring Real back to 42-49 at break.
</P>
<P>
Real fought on to make it 71-74 after scoring 12 points
without reply with seven minutes left.
</P>
<P>
But Barcelona increased its lead to 94-82 at last, shattering
Real's hope to make a comeback.
</P>
<P>
In the day's another match of Group A in Athens, Greece,
Germany's Leverkusen upset hosts Iraklis 81-72.
</P>
<P>
Leverkusen ranked fifth in Group A while Iraklis was on the
bottom with 12. 
</P>
</TEXT>
