<HEADLINE> Hungarian Peacekeepers Leave for Bosnia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, January 17 (Xinhua) -- An 80-member advance team of
Hungarian peacekeeping troops left this afternoon for Okucani in
Croatia, which borders on Bosnia, according to the local media.
</P>
<P>
Hungarian President Arpad Gonoz went to the railway station in
Ercsi, southwest of Budapest, to see them off.
</P>
<P>
The main part of Hungarian peacekeeping force, with more than
300 members, is scheduled to go to Okucani, where the peacekeepers
will have their barracks, on January 26 and will start their
mission in Bosnia on February 1.
</P>
<P>
The mission of the Hungarian troops, who are all technical
personnel, is to build roads and bridges on the Sava River.
