<DATE_TIME> 1996-01-18 02:19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Inflation Drops in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Inflation in Albania dropped to
7.5 percent in 1995 from 400 percent in 1991, an Albanian
economist said here today.
</P>
<P>
Economist Fatos Gogoli said that the inflation rate is expected
to decline further this year with the increase in investment and
national economic recovery.
</P>
<P>
Gogoli attributed the decline to the increase of investment in
production and commercial sectors, the government's strict control
on money supply and the recovery and development of agricultural,
animal husbandry and food processing industries.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, the investments made by Albanians, foreigners and
overseas Albanians totaled 120 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the remittances sent by Albanians working in foreign
countries, about 400 million dollars every year, also played an
important role in the economic development.
</P>
<P>
There are 450,000 Albanians working abroad, accounting for 14
percent of the country's total population. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
