<HEADLINE> China's Mineral-Rich Pacific Ocean Territory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 18 (Xinhua)-- China's right to develop a
part of the Pacific Ocean bed that is rich in metallic mineral
resources, sufficient to satisfy Chinese needs for many years, has
been recognized as by the UN, according to Chinese oceanographers.
</P>
<P>
An announcement was made by Chinese officials about China's
right to develop the piece of sea bed, that covers 105,000 sq.km,
was recognized by the United Nations for China's pioneering
exploratory work on a 300,000-sq.-km patch of the Pacific Ocean
bed.
</P>
<P>
Four Pacific scientific expeditions have been carried out by
the China Ocean Society (COS) since the early 1980s. The latest
one finished its work late last year after a five month survey of
the ocean area.
</P>
<P>
COS was set up in 1990 with the approval of the Chinese
government to specialize in multi-metallic structure exploration
and international co-operation in deep sea mineral extraction.
enditem

18/01/96 02:07 GMT
nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
