<HEADLINE> Former Romanian Leader's Children Confirmed Innocent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, January 17 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian General
Procuratorate has announced that executed former Romanian leader
Nicolae Ceausescu's sons and daughter did not commit "the crime
of jeopardizing the national economy."
</P>
<P>
Local press reports said today that the procuratorate had
decided to drop criminal suits against Ceausescu's two sons,
Nicu and Balentir, and his daughter, Zoia.
</P>
<P>
Without mentioning when the procuratorate made the decision,
the reports also said all confiscated personal property will be
returned to them.
</P>
<P>
Ceausescu and his wife were executed secretly in December 1989
in a military coup and one of the charges against the couple was
"jeopardizing the national economy."
</P>
<P>
The two sons' former wives and the daughter's former husband
were also acquitted on the charges.
</P>
<P>
Nicu, Ceausescu's only descendant engaged in politics till his
overthrow, was jailed and sentenced to 20 years in prison but
released in November 1992 due to his serious illness. 
</P>
</TEXT>
