<DATE_TIME> 1996-01-18 00:59 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unemployment Rate Down in Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, January 17 (Xinhua) -- The National Institute of
Statistics, Geography and Computer Database (INEGI) said today
that the unemployment rate in Mexico in January declined for the
fourth month in a row.
</P>
<P>
Unemployment began to decrease in the last quarter of 1995
when it dropped from 7.3 percent in September to 6.7 percent in
October and from 5.8 percent in November to 5.2 percent in
December, the organization said.
</P>
<P>
Of the total jobless in the country, 84.6 percent said they had
some work experience and 15.4 percent had none.
</P>
<P>
The institute said 94.8 percent of the people had jobs up till
December 1995 with 37.2 percent in the service sector, 21.8
percent in commerce, 20.9 percent in manufacturing, 6.3 percent in
communications, 6 percent in the government and 7.8 percent in
other fields. 
</P>
</TEXT>
