<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Build Holiday Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Although the number of
tourists in Shanghai, China's largest city, is growing, most
people still go there for shopping and business purposes and
complain about its shortage of natural scenery.
</P>
<P>
To put an end to its reputation as being solely a commercial
center, a 50-sq-km holiday zone is scheduled to be built. It will
be in the northern part of Songjiang County, 30 km from the urban
area, between National Highway No. 318 and 320, in the only place
with woods and forests in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen wrote the
name for the Sheshan State Tourism and Holiday Zone. Projects for
the zone include amusement areas, villas, agriculture, services,
colleges, and the tourist industry. A golf course, forest park, an
outer space science and technology town, and a folklore garden are
to be built soon.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, the zone is expected to be
completed by the turn of the century, to receive 5.4 million
visitors annually.  
</P>
</TEXT>
