<HEADLINE> More Women Artists Win Prizes in 1995 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 18 (Xinhua) -- One-third of the winners at the
3rd national oil painting art show held here recently were women.
</P>
<P>
A large number of works by women artists, including traditional
Chinese paintings, oil paintings, calligraphy, sculptures, and
other works, provided an attraction during the Fourth World
Conference on Women, which was the largest event in U.N. history
held in China, last year.
</P>
<P>
