<HEADLINE> UK's Unemployment Lowest Since May 1991 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Britain's unemployment which has
been seasonally adjusted is now at its lowest level since May
1991, after dropping for the 28th month in a row, BBC TV reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The figure for the number of people out of work and receiving
unemployment benefit dropped by 7,900 to 2,236,900.
</P>
<P>
Now Britain had a jobless rate of eight percent.
</P>
<P>
Education and emlpoyment minister Eric Forth said that
Britain's deregulated labour market, tight control on public
spending and low taxes were delivering economic growth and jobs.
</P>
<P>
the UK had one of the lowest unemployment rate in the European
Union, he said.
</P>
<P>
Unemployment in Germany stood at 8.5 percent, in France and
Italy at 11.5 percent and in Spain at 22.5 percent, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
