<HEADLINE> Russian Forces Continue Attack on Chechen Terrorists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 17 (Xinhua) -- Russian joint forces continued
their attack against Chechen terrorists still holding several
dozens of hostages in the Daghestani village of Pervomaiskoye
today, ccording to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the headquarters in charge of the hostage
rescue operation in Pervomaiskoye near the Daghestani-Chechen
border told reporters that 41 hostages had been rescued by this
evening.
</P>
<P>
The Russian forces lost 13 men killed and over 40 injured.
</P>
<P>
Russian forces' artillery and helicopters made a number of
strikes on "well-fortified" terrorists positions in the center
of the village, the spokesman said. Special units carried out a
combat reconnaissance mission this afternoon, but failed to
alter the disposition of forces and free more hostages, he
added.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman confirmed that the Chechen terrorists in
Pervomaiskoye were 250 to 300 men strong when the fighting
started on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The terrorists are reportedly equipped with grenade launchers
and big-calibre machine-guns with piles and piles of ammunition.
"They can hold on forever. They will not leave anyone alive.
They will show mercy for neither themselves nor anyone else,"
Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
However, the Russian forces expressed that they are ready
to wipe out the terrorists in Pervomaiskoye. 
</P>
</TEXT>
