<HEADLINE> Volcano in Cape Verde Erupts again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 17 (Xinhua) -- The Pico de Fogo, a volcano on
an island in southern Cape Verde, released visible fumes today
after becoming active again at the weekend since its last
eruptions in April 1995, PANA reported from Praia today.
</P>
<P>
Tremors were recorded at Cha Das Caldermujla Settlement near
the volcano, when the emissions started, reported the Pan African
News Agency (PANA) from the Cape Verdian capital.
</P>
<P>
No incidents have been reported so far. However, some 5,000
people near the volcano were displaced during its April 1995
eruptions.
</P>
<P>
PANA said a team of four Cape Verdian geologists had visited
the area on Monday to monitor the volcano's developments. 
</P>
