<HEADLINE> Chinese Delegation Visits UN Headquarters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, January 18 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese delegation
composed officials from the State Science and Technology
Commission, the State Planning Commission and the Ministry of
Foreign Economic Cooperation and Trade visited the United Nations
headquarters in New York recently.
</P>
<P>
The visit is aimed at promoting regional economic development
along the trunk railway line known as the New Eurasian Continental
Bridge. The railway winds its way from Lianyungang Port in east
China across Xinjiang in west China to European countries.
</P>
<P>
The delegation headed by Rui Xingwen met with James Gustave
Speth, the Administrator of the the United Nations Development
Programme (UNDP), Jichaozhu, Under-Secretary-General and other
officers of the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
When meeting with Speth, Rui said that making good use of the
New Eurasian Continental Bridge will strengthen the economic and
technological cooperation and promote economic development along
the railway line, and consolidate peace and friendship among
European and Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has decided to give priority to the
opening and development of the area along the continental bridge
and will actively participate in regional and international
cooperation and development along the new continental bridge.
</P>
<P>
Speth said that promotion of economic development of the
Eurasian Continental Bridge region is an exciting project and the
UNDP will support the project.  
</P>
</TEXT>
