<HEADLINE> Syrian President Welcomes French Role in Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Syrian President Hafez
al-Assad today welcomed an effective French role in the Middle
East peace process.
</P>
<P>
According to Syrian presidential spokesman Jibran Kourieh,
President al-Assad said during his meeting here with visiting
French Foreign Minister Herve de Charette that Syria always
expects France to play an effective role that will help push
forward the peace process towards its cherished target.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian president also pointed out that a just and
comprehensive peace in the region is a Syrian objective, adding
that peace could only be achieved through implementing the
U.N. resolutions concerned and respecting the rights of all
parties.
</P>
<P>
President al-Assad discussed with the visiting French foreign
minister the situation in the region and the peace process. The
French minister expressed his country's desire to play a more
extensive and effective role in the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Al-Assad and de Charette Also reviewed Syrian-French relations,
and President al-Assad welcomed the boosting of cooperation
between the two countries in the best interest of the two parties.
</P>
<P>
The French foreign minister left for home today after winding
up his two-day visit to Syria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
