<HEADLINE> Syrian President Meets with French Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, January 18 (Xinhua) -- Syrian President Hafez
al-Assad held here today a two-hour talk with visiting French
Foreign Minister Herve de Charette, with the presence of Syrian
Foreign Minister Farouq al-Shara.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference joint held with his French
counterpart following the meeting, al-Shara described the meeting
as "important and good."
</P>
<P>
The Syrian foreign minister said that the French Minister's
visit to Syria is successful and has contributed to the promotion
of Syrian-French relations in political, economic and cultural
fields.
</P>
<P>
He said the discussion covered the latest developments of the
Middle East peace process, the prospects of the coming round of
Syrian-Israeli negotiations later this month, the future situation
in the region and the French role in the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Al-Shara added that both sides spelled out the necessity of
boosting relations between Syria and the European Union in
general and France in particular.
</P>
<P>
On his part, de Charette said his country was determined to
take a more active role in the Middle East peace process and in
the region.
</P>
<P>
He added that "France is coming back indeed ... and is
determined to present with its proposals and its cordial position.
</P>
<P>
Also today, De Charette had also had talks with al-Shara on the
situation in the region, the developments of the peace process,
Syria's relations with the European Union, as well as ways to
promote Syrian-French ties in various fields.
</P>
<P>
The French foreign minister has left here for home today after
a two-day visit to Syria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
